06/03/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Ahead of next Sunday's (13 March) local elections, a new poll finds that the ruling Social Democratic Alliance of Macedonia (SDSM) holds a moderate lead.
According to results released Friday, 15.3 per cent of the respondents said they would back SDSM.
The main opposition party VMRO-DPMNE was second with 10.5 per cent, followed by the Democratic Union for Integration, with 10.3 per cent.
The poll was conducted by the Institute for Sociological and Political-Legal Research between 25 February and 28 February.
It also found that nearly 20 per cent of voters remain undecided, while 12.7 per cent said they would not go to the polls.
(Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik - 05/03/05)
